<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Written evidence submitted by The University of Manchester (WSC014)</title></head><body><div><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence submitted by The University of Manchester (WSC014)</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">1. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The University of Manchester has nearly 40,000 students and more than 10,000 staff. The University is committed to creating an environment where diversity is celebrated and everyone is treated fairly regardless of gender, disability, ethnic origin, religio</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">n or belief, sexual orientation, marital status, age or nationality.  </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">2.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We are taking positive steps to achieve equality in the workplace and are committed to both meeting and exceeding our obligations under current legislation. As an academic instituti</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">on we believe that women are vital to the world of academia, and therefore find it relevant to respond to this inquiry.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">3</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Why do you think the number of women in STEM academic careers decline further up the career ladder? </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">3.1</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Work-life Balance:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Whether we like it or not, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">women often carry the majority of childcare responsibility within the family and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">sometimes</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> it</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">c</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">an</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> be difficult to maintain an</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> academic career </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">whilst</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> raising </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">a family or having other significant</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> caring duties/o</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">bligations. Having </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">children</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> etc, does inhibit opportunity to go abroad to conferences, etc, (activity which helps CV and promotion prospects), particularly if the academic female does not have other support around (at home).</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Further, hours are often long and there is a lack </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">of flexible/part time working opportunities giving the perception that there is not a healthy work life balance amongst academic </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">staff.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Where flexibility or part-time worki</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ng does exist there is a perception</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">that career</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> progress</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ion is more difficult,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> as qu</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">antity is valued and quality alone is not enough.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> For those women who decide not to raise a family there are still issues which include structural issues, bias etc.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">3.2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Recognition:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Women can </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">be engaged in a disproportionate number of service </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">activities t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">hat benefit the School, for example being an admissions/year tutor</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">as a result</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> may not</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> have the capacity to work on activities that would better serve </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">promotion</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> prospects</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The achievements </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">women </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">can be left </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">unrecognised because </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">in general, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">women are often </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">less good at </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">market</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> themselves </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">than men</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">A recent study of research abstracts by Ohio State University demonstrates</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> that both female and male students believe that papers written by women are of lower quality than papers written by men. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Women therefore need to ‘outperform’ men to gain appropriate recognition.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">3.3</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Lack of Confidence:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> W</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">omen generally take longer </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">or are more cautious about applying</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> for promo</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">tion as they want to make sure they meet </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">every criterion fully before submitting an </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">application.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">3.4</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Lack of Opportunities:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Recruitment processes can be </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">problematic;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> especially the higher up the ladder one goes. For example, ‘search committees’ are often </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">dominated by men who only access</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> their own networks (which usually are made up of other men) so potential female candidates do not get identified or approached early on in the recruitment process. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">A bigger issue is that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">many senior academic roles do not</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> even have search committees.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">3.5</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Career Breaks:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Any career breaks that do take place seem to affect career paths</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and the working environment is not always sensitive or accommodating to individual circumstances. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">3.6</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Lack of Role Models:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> The number of female guest speakers and images of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">women on display is minimal or non-existent which means there is a lack of visible role models.  Women are often not encouraged by peers to network and be at the fore-front of the School.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Further, there is a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">distinct lack of successful female role models w</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ith families which </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">can create a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> perception that it is not possible for academics to combine a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> successful career </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">with a family</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">3.7</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Unconscious Bias</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">: As a result of unconscious bias often similar people to that of the recruiter</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">(s)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> are employed which leads </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to a culture where there is not a diverse range of people, often with white males dominating.  Many institutions are starting to deliver training on this but there can be a lack of take-up of this training by those who need it most.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Unconscious bias also e</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">xtends to matters including lack of invitations to speak at seminars or international conferences – such invitations are important to promotion. This is a common problem.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">3.8</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Leadership Style:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Women </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">often perceive that aggressive political skills are required at </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the top of the career ladder </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">or in positions of authority, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">as they </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">may </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">not want to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">adopt this </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">style of leadership</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Not </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">always, but often the male dominated leadership style can be aggressive a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">nd riddled with unconscious bias.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">3.9</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Lack of Mentoring Opportunities:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Mentoring</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> to early career researchers</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> is often performed by senior academics on an informal basis. Senior academics are usually male, and either consciously or unconsciously t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">hey t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">end </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to choose people similar to themselves (i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">e. males) to mentor.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">3.10</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Lack of Career Structure:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Career progression, for example by publication, funding and collaborations are difficult if you have a career break (e.g. maternity leave) and it is important that institutions help women returning from maternity leave to get their research career back on </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">track. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Moreover, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the structural problem</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> whereby postdoctoral researchers</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">are required to complete </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">a series of fixed term positions before </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">starting a permanent academic career track can dissuade women</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. Contracts that are offered to women are usually short t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">erm which means female academics have to move around Universities more often</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, which is not </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ideal, especially for those who wish to stay in one place so that they can raise children</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, or have commitments as family carers</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. Further, there is a perception that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">there is not a healthy work life balance amongst academic staff and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">that women are drawn to industry where </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the pay is much better</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">3.11</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Examples of supporting STEM academic women at The University of Manchester:</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">3.12 </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The University of Manchester is commi</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">tted to Athena SWAN Charter for Women in Science and its principles. The University has held a Bronze Award since 2008 and s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">o far, four awards are held by Schools. The other eleven STEMM Schools are currently working towards awards, with the support of the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> dedicated University’s Athena SWAN Coordinator and a commitment to making a long term cultural change which will benefit all staff.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">3.13 </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">P</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ublicity </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">materials </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">depict both men and women and</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> during Open Days for potential students</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> female staff speak at events, conduct interviews and show round candidates. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">3.14 </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Faculty-wide Academic Promotions Masterclass workshops are d</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">elivered every year, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">and are advertised with a positive action statement to encourage women to attend</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">suppor</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">t staff in submitting promotion cases. Furthermore Schools offer CV clinics for individually tailored support. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">3.15 </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">U</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">nconscious bias training </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">has been delivered </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">for the benefit of those on recruitment/promotion panels, to raise awareness of this issue an</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">d for them to consider their own biases during recruitment/promotion processes. This is being developed to be included in mandatory recruitment and selection training for all recruiters.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">3.16 </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">he University of Manchester </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">has </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">strong network groups for staf</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">f and students, including a Peer Support Group for Women Returning from Maternity Leave, International Staff Network Group and Women in Science, Engineering and Technology (WiSET). The groups organise events throughout the year and the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">U</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">niversity allows me</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">mbers up to eight hours per year to be dedicated to network group activities from their standard working hours. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">3.17 </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> University of Manchester </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">has</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> a number of family-friendly policies including flexible working,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> career break and special leave. F</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">amily-friendly support includes childcare initiatives to help reduce costs with a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">salary exchange scheme for paying for childcare, childcare vouchers and two on site nurseries. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">3.18</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Our Faculty of Medical and Human Sciences has established a Fellowship Ac</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ademy that provides concentrated support for those people wanting to secure fellowships.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">4.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">When women leave academia, what careers do they transition into? </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.1 </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Women often work in industry</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, the NHS</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> or for a government agency after they le</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ave academia.  Alternatively </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">women </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">tend to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">develop careers in</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> communications</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and human resources. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">5.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">What are the consequences of scientifically trained women applying their skills in different employment sectors?</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.1</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Loss of highly trained and highly </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">skilled people:</span><span style="color:#1f497d; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Lo</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">sing a high proportion of the bright and skilled population overall, often into jobs that do not take full advantage of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">their </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">skills and training (there is strong evidence that women have pay that is on average much worse than men with eq</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">uivalent qualifications)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">is bad for the UK economy.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Loss of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> role models in academia</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> There is a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">lready a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> distinct lack of successful f</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">emale role models (including those with families) </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">so </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">female </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">graduates </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">perceive</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> academia as somewhere not to have a successful career and a family. In addition graduates do not get the opportunity to talk to academics to see what it is like to pursue an academic career</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and with women moving into industry, the prevalence of advice fro</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">m women would decrease further</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. It is often assumed that graduates have knowledge about career choices, but this is not always the case, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">and</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">so</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> career support is needed, including talks from female academics</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">3</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Industry will be</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> seen as the natural progr</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">ession for women (not academia)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">: </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">If students are not able to identify themselves with</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">staff at the University </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">they </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">will choose</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> to work elsewhere following their graduation. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Many go into teaching or non-STE</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">M</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">M related careers.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Male domination:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Statistics show</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> that academia is often crowded by</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> senior</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> male academics. Losing women to different employment sectors will only make </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">this situation </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">worse and further</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> will enhance the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">stereotype that only men are suitable for academic positions in STEM</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">M</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Lack of diversity </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">in higher education:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Diversity is a business driver and there is real evidence around diverse teams leading to better </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">organisational</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> performance</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">6</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Decrease in ideas and innovation</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">A diverse group of people is needed to progress </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">and deliver the best. It has been proven that people from similar backgrounds have similar thinking patterns and therefore</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> fail to produce novel policies and ideas</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. Diversity is </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">a prime</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> catalyst for new ideas and innovation and therefore the retention of w</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">omen in academia is greatly needed.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">To retain women in academia, The University of Manchester offers the following:</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">7</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Equality and Diversity Training:  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">All </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">members of staff are required to complete an online equality and diversity training module. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> This is </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">included as part of the induction for new members of staff. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">8</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Unconscious Bias Training: </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Unconscious bias training has been</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> delivered to those on recruitment/promotion panels, to raise awareness of this issue and for them to consider their own</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> biases during recruitment/promotion processes. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">This is currently being developed to be included in</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> mandatory recruitment and selection training for all recruiters.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">9</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Research Time:  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Academics returning from maternity leave are offered a 6 month period, in which they are relieved of teaching duties so that they can focus on their research work. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.1</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">0</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Generous Maternity Leave</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">/Support</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">: </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The University </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">offers a substantial maternity leave</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> package which includes 6 months full pay, plus 3 months statutory pay.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Whilst on maternity leave the University offers 5 ‘keeping in touch’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> days, which are paid and</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">not t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">aken out of the maternity leave period</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The University also has a staff network </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">group specifically for those returning to</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> work after having a child</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> for additional support. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">6.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">What should universities and the higher education sector do to retain women graduates and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">PhD</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> students in academic careers?</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">6.1</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Career Support:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Clear career advice should be available which is sensitive to diversity and gender and a clear career structure should be provided detailing what career paths they can take so that they can make an informed decision about their career choice. Improved inf</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ormation and communication on internal jobs, and accessibility to positions is critical, to increase the chances of the graduate/PhD Student remaining at the institution.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">6.2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">PI Support:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Principal Investigators should be better supported to understand and</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> deliver mentoring &amp; career advice as this is often the person the graduates look to for support. It is important that PIs are involved with the Researcher Development Team so they are able to offer the graduates all the opportunities open to them. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">6.3</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">N</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">etworking:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Improve opportunities for networking so graduates/students have the chance to meet early career researchers/lecturers and hear their stories about how they made the transition from student to staff. Cross-faculty and multi-disciplinary events op</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">en more doors across the University where they would be able to work based on their expertise in particular fields.  </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">6.4</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Role Models:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Showcase and celebrate successful female academics.  Ensure that conferences, seminars and events include female speaker</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s wherever possible.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">6.5</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Communication:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Ensure staff and students are aware of the policies in place to help support women so concerns from students can be answered quickly or found out easily. Running events where women graduates can see/hear that it is </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">possible to be a mother and an academic and highlighting the support available following maternity leave is important. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">6.6</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Work-life balance:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> We need to look at the environment within higher education where the long hours culture still dominates.  If we </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">want to encourage and retain women then we need to do more to support those who want to work part-time, flexibly or take a career break and for there to be opportunities for</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> them to progress their career.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> We also need to stop the long-hours culture</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> to show</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> it </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">is possible to work successfully whil</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">st</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> retaining a work-life balance.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">6.7</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">The University of Manchester supports females who wish to pursue an academic career in the following ways:   </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The University </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">h</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">as forums and networks for graduates and stud</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ents </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to share their experiences with each other and staff. There are also</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> formal mentoring schemes where students are linked with an experienced member of staff and schemes where students can assist their peers. Other examples of good practice we have to ensure</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> that women progress into academic careers</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> are listed below in 7</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">7. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Have you any example of good practice? </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Forums for graduates and students to share experiences </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">For example at The University of Manchester we have:</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:5pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">7.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">1</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Women in Science, Engineering </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">and Technology (WiSET):</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">A network for all female students, research and academic staff in the Faculty of Engineering and Physical Sciences.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:5pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">7.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Women in Life Sciences:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> A</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">developing network for all female academic and research staff, administrative staff an</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">d students within Life Sciences at The University of Manchester.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:5pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">7.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">3</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Women in I.T.:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">A</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> networking forum for women at all grades working in IT across the University.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:5pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">7.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Networking </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">: </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">For example at The University of Manchester we have:</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:5pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">7.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">School PhD and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">PDRA Forums:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Students &amp; Research Staff from different research groups in the School can meet regularly (usually once a quarter) to see what others are doing and share experiences. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:5pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">7.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">6</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">EPS Ambassadors: </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">PDRAs engage cross-faculty</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">which opens up opportunitie</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s for research in different Schools</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:5pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">7.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">7</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Research Staff Association:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Open to researchers across the University (4 Faculties) to share experiences about life as a researcher and to discuss topics of interest (for example: fixed term contracts, open access pu</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">blishing and extended access). Manchester RSA actively engages with Vitae’s UK Research Staff Association (UKRSA). The first RSA Manchester Mini Sandpit was organised in 2012 which was a compressed version of the interactive, multidisciplinary workshops us</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ed by funding bodies to drive lateral thinking and radical approaches to research challenges.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">All research forums work with the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Researcher Development Team</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> at The University of Manchester and there are a number of funds available, such as the “School Resea</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">rch Conferences Fund”, the “Researcher Led Initiatives Fund” and the “External Training Fund” to support local initiatives. A recent event (March 2013) funded by the Researcher Led Initiative, “</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Life after post doc: What can </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">happen next?”,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">was organised by </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">School of Physics and Astronomy Researcher Development Forum where researchers and fellows from the School heard stories from four speakers from academia, industry and the public sector to help researchers understand the different options open to them </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">after their current positions finish.  </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">7.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">8</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Mentoring schemes</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">For example at The University of Manchester we have:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">7.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">9</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Manchester Gold Mentoring Scheme: </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Students are matched on a one to one basis with an experienced member of staff (a mentor) and will be</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> in contact with them over a nine month period. The programme aims to help students with career planning and decision making about their future options</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">7.1</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">0</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Peer Assisted Study Sessions (PASS): </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">A Student Learning Scheme</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">that is ran by students and provid</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">es a facilitated, group learning opportunity that uses the experiences of higher year students to support the learning of lower year peers</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">7.11</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The University of Manchester also provides a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">‘Buddy System’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> which links PhD students to a PDRA.  In some Schoo</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ls PhD students and PDRAs in the same research group share an office to help facilitate this and allow for everyday interaction between staff and students.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">7.1</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Career service</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The University of Manchester provides a career service to all students during </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">their studies and for two years after they graduate. In 2011 the careers service won the 'Times Higher Education Award for Outstanding Support for Early Career Researchers' for their dedicated academic career website for PhD and research staff. Recently (F</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ebruary 2013) the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Head of Post Graduate Career Development offered advice to students about PhD applications and career prospects in academic field, at the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Faculty wide WiSET event, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Is an Academic Career for You</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">8</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">What role should the Government have </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">in encouraging the retention of women in academic STEM careers?</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">8.1 </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The government must offer support and recognition for women who juggle academic commitments and family commitments. Better maternity leave support from funding bodies should be provided s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">o that all the support does not have to come through the University</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. W</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">omen need see that they can have a career break, return to work and go on to further their career. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">8.2 </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">It would also greatly help if there was better support for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">partners</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> in terms of l</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">eave so that a couple can jointly care for their child, without the woman missing out on key progression points in her career.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">8.3 </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Programmes such as Athena SWAN should be more heavily invested in by the Government as they make a considerable impact on the number of departments that work towards gender equality. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">August 2013</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>